description: Get detail data for Proton account-wide settings.

nested_items.name: accountSettings
nested_items.description: The Proton pipeline service role detail data that's returned by Proton.

nested_items.name: pipelineCodebuildRoleArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the service role that Proton uses for provisioning pipelines. Proton assumes this role for CodeBuild-based provisioning.

nested_items.name: pipelineProvisioningRepository
nested_items.description: The linked repository for pipeline provisioning. Required if you have environments configured for self-managed provisioning with services that include pipelines. A linked repository is a repository that has been registered with Proton. For more information, see  CreateRepository.

nested_items.name: arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the linked repository.

nested_items.name: pipelineServiceRoleArn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the service role you want to use for provisioning pipelines. Assumed by Proton for Amazon Web Services-managed provisioning, and by customer-owned automation for self-managed provisioning.
